# PROJECT CONTEXT
This repository is a Grasshopper plugin for AI-assisted structural optimization of roof systems
(Dachkonstruktion). It extends the "text-to-code" methodology from prior research on truss
optimization to roof typologies: ridge beams, hip/valley rafters, purlins, and node elements.

## Architecture Overview

The workflow is entirely Grasshopper-native. n8n is used ONLY offline to populate the
Pinecone vector database (chunking + embedding documents). At runtime, Grasshopper talks
directly to Pinecone and the LLM API via HTTP — no n8n involved.

```
[n8n — offline, one-time setup only]
  Google Drive (papers + code snippets)
    → chunk → embed (use a non-OpenAI embedding provider; this project is Claude-only)
    → Pinecone namespace

[Grasshopper — runtime, everything else]
  User prompt (GH Panel)
    → RAG Query Component (GHPython)
        HTTP POST to Pinecone /query
        returns top-k relevant chunks
    → LLM Generation Component (GHPython)
        HTTP POST to Anthropic Claude API only (no OpenAI)
        system prompt + retrieved context + user prompt
        returns Python script as string
    → Script Execution Component (GHPython)
        exec() the generated script in CPython 3
        captures JSON output string
    → Geometry Builder Component (GHPython)
        parses JSON → Rhino.Geometry.Line / Point3d
    → Karamba3D components (native GH)
        cross section, material, supports, loads
        FEM solver, visualization
```

## Current setup: Python-only (Option A)

All logic runs as GHPython scripts loaded via exec(open("path/to/script.py").read(), ctx).
No C# components yet. Scripts live in 03_python/; edit in IDE, save, Recompute in GH.

(Optional future: PRODUCTION layer as compiled C# components in /src/ mirroring this logic.)

