# ENVIRONMENT & DEPENDENCIES

## Python (03_python/ and 03_python/tests/)
- Runtime: CPython 3.9+ (Rhino 8 ScriptEditor — select "CPython 3" in component settings)
- Standard library only for HTTP: urllib.request, json, os, sys, io
- Scientific: numpy, scipy (available in Rhino 8 CPython environment)
- Rhino/GH available when running inside GH: import Rhino, Rhino.Geometry as rg
- Karamba API available in GH: import clr; clr.AddReference("KarambaCommon")
- For standalone testing: guard Rhino imports with try/except ImportError
- NEVER use: requests, pinecone SDK, openai SDK, anthropic SDK — use urllib.request only. LLM = Claude (Anthropic) only, no OpenAI.
- NEVER use: pandas, matplotlib (not in Rhino 8 env by default)
- API keys: from .env at repo root; 03_python/config/settings.py uses python-dotenv to load into os.environ

## config/settings.py (03_python/config/; gitignored)
Copy from settings.example.py. Loads .env from repo root (parents[2]). Claude only.

## C# (future /src/)
- Not used in Option A. When added: net48, Grasshopper SDK, same patterns as in cursorrules.

---

# CODING CONVENTIONS

## Python scripts (03_python/)
- Physical units: meters for geometry, kN for forces, MPa for stress, cm² for cross-sections
- Every function has a docstring stating: inputs, outputs, units, algorithm reference
- JSON output: always via print(json.dumps(...)) at the end of main(), never intermediate prints
- Error handling: raise ValueError with descriptive messages — GHPython catches and shows in component
- Guard Rhino imports: `try: import Rhino; HAS_RHINO = True \nexcept ImportError: HAS_RHINO = False`
- Scripts must work in BOTH contexts: inside GH (Rhino available) and standalone pytest (Rhino absent)
- Type hints required on all function signatures (PEP 484)

---

# STRUCTURAL DOMAIN KNOWLEDGE

## Roof Typology Conventions
- Gable roof: ridge beam along centerline, rafters from ridge to wall plates, purlins optional
- Hip roof: ridge + hip rafters at ~45° to corners, jack rafters infilling
- Coordinate system: X = span direction, Y = longitudinal direction, Z = vertical (up)
- Support conditions: pinned at wall plate nodes (all translation DOFs fixed, rotations free)
- Loads (DIN EN 1991-1-3/1-4): snow 0.8–2.0 kN/m², wind varies, self-weight from section

## Optimization Algorithms in Use
- BESO: topology optimization — iteratively remove low-stress members from ground structure
- Iterative Sizing: proportional area redistribution, constant total volume
- Ground Structure Method: dense initial mesh, converge to efficient topology
- All generated scripts: implement main() and end with print(json.dumps(result))

## Karamba3D (inside GH, GHPython)
- Always use Karamba factory/builder pattern — never instantiate Karamba objects directly
- Key inputs to Assemble Model: geometry (lines), supports, cross-sections, materials, loads
- Output from Analyze: displacement, utilization, internal forces per member

---

# WHAT TO GENERATE vs. NOT

## Always generate:
- Standalone-testable Python functions with docstrings and type hints
- urllib.request-based HTTP calls (never requests or SDK imports)
- try/except guards around Rhino imports for testability
- Test stubs in 03_python/tests/ for new optimization functions
- 03_python/config/settings.example.py entries for any new environment variables

## Never generate:
- Hardcoded API keys or absolute file paths
- Intermediate print() calls in scripts (only the final JSON print)
- IronPython 2.7 syntax (xrange, print statement, unicode literals u"...")
- JSON that deviates from 03_python/schemas/structural_output.json
- requests, openai, anthropic, pinecone library imports — use urllib.request only; LLM = Claude (Anthropic) only
- n8n workflow modifications — n8n is READ-ONLY for RAG ingestion, not runtime
